AB  - To identify the sedimentary environment characteristics and the genesis of black rocks in Upper Permian Dalong Formation, Hefeng area, Hubei province, the detailed element geochemistry of black rocks was analyzed in Well HD1. The results show that the reducing environment of Dalong Formation is the key control factor of organic matter enrichment. The early sedimentary was relatively stable as the reducing environment with lean oxygen and rich H 2 S, while the mid-late sedimentary presented the oxygen lean-oxygen deficit environment with significant fluctuations. In the sedimentary period of Dalong Formation, the upwelling development provided a lot of nutrient-rich materials, leading to the oxygen deficit environment in sedimentary water mass and the high paleo-productivity. The upwelling of thermal water along the contemporaneous faults had no adverse effect on the development of shale gas, which mainly caused the formation of authigenic dolomite and albite, the dissolution and re-cementation of siliceous organisms and the promotion of thermal evolution on organic matters. The layered silicalite locally developed in Dalong Formation are of two genetic types, i. e., biological genesis and authigenic chemical precipitation. © 2018, Editorial Office of ACTA PETROLEI SINICA. All right reserved.
